{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_87","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve mapped the upstream surfaces. The implementation is going into a new `dashboard_session_planning` library module that will:\n\n1. Resolve one session from three entry modes:\n   - manifest-driven: reuse simulation and analysis planning plus existing bundle discovery\n   - experiment-driven: discover contract-backed analysis/validation metadata and require unambiguous bundle selection unless selectors are provided\n   - explicit bundle-driven: validate the supplied baseline, wave, analysis, and validation metadata against one another\n\n2. Normalize one session plan:\n   - choose one baseline/wave arm pair and one canonical simulator bundle pair\n   - validate shared timebase, shared readout comparability, shared input identity, and geometry availability\n   - assemble pane inputs for scene, circuit, morphology, time-series, and analysis\n   - compute overlay availability and deterministic dashboard-session output paths through `dashboard_session_contract`\n\n3. Package the session:\n   - write `dashboard_session.json`\n   - write a real `dashboard_session_payload.json` with normalized pane inputs and artifact refs\n   - write `session_state.json`\n   - write a deterministic placeholder `app/index.html` so the bundle surface is complete before FW-M14-003\n\n4. Add regression coverage:\n   - deterministic manifest fixture assembly and packaging\n   - override precedence via preferred seed/condition selection\n   - clear failures for incompatible timebases, missing wave diagnostics for a requested overlay, and missing morphology assets\n\n5. Add `docs/ui_dashboard_notes/FW-M14-002_rationale.md` explaining the design, tests, and deliberate simplifications."}}
